Fix twitter-cli search: x.com → x.com/home

twitter-cli's ClientTransaction init fetches https://x.com (logged-out page)
to find the ondemand.s.*.js file. Twitter removed this from the logged-out
page in mid-2026, causing:

  WARNING: Failed to init ClientTransaction: 'NoneType' object has no attribute 'group'

Without ClientTransaction, the x-client-transaction-id header is missing,
and the SearchTimeline GraphQL endpoint returns 404.

Fix: fetch https://x.com/home (authenticated page) which still has the
ondemand JS reference and loading-x-anim elements.

Applies to: twitter-cli 0.8.5 (xclienttransaction 1.0.3)
File: site-packages/twitter_cli/client.py, line ~1074

--- a/site-packages/twitter_cli/client.py
+++ b/site-packages/twitter_cli/client.py
@@ -1071,7 +1071,7 @@
             cffi_session = _get_cffi_session()
             ct_headers = _gen_ct_headers()
             home_page = cffi_session.get(
-                "https://x.com", headers=ct_headers, timeout=10,
+                "https://x.com/home", headers=ct_headers, timeout=10,
             )
             home_page_response = bs4.BeautifulSoup(home_page.content, "html.parser")
